## Memory Leaks Prevention

### Event Listeners
- Always remove event listeners when done
- Use weak references when appropriate
- Limit the number of listeners

### Streams
- Properly close streams after use
- Handle stream errors
- Use pipeline for better error handling

### Example
```typescript
import { pipeline } from 'stream';
import { promisify } from 'util';

const pipelineAsync = promisify(pipeline);

async processFile(filePath: string) {
  const readStream = createReadStream(filePath);
  const writeStream = createWriteStream(outputPath);

  try {
    await pipelineAsync(readStream, transformStream, writeStream);
  } catch (error) {
    // Streams are automatically closed on error
    throw error;
  }
}
```

## Monitoring and Profiling

### Performance Monitoring
- Implement request logging with duration
- Monitor memory usage
- Track database query performance
- Use APM tools (Application Performance Monitoring)

### Example - Logging Interceptor
```typescript
@Injectable()
export class LoggingInterceptor implements NestInterceptor {
  intercept(context: ExecutionContext, next: CallHandler): Observable<any> {
    const now = Date.now();
    const request = context.switchToHttp().getRequest();

    return next.handle().pipe(
      tap(() => {
        const duration = Date.now() - now;
        console.log(`${request.method} ${request.url} - ${duration}ms`);
      }),
    );
  }
}
```

### Health Checks
- Implement health check endpoints
- Monitor database connectivity
- Check external service availability
- Monitor memory and CPU usage

### Example
```typescript
@Controller('health')
export class HealthController {
  constructor(
    private health: HealthCheckService,
    private db: TypeOrmHealthIndicator,
  ) {}

  @Get()
  @HealthCheck()
  check() {
    return this.health.check([
      () => this.db.pingCheck('database'),
    ]);
  }
}
```

