## Code Optimization

### Lazy Loading
- Use lazy loading for modules when appropriate
- Defer loading of heavy dependencies
- Load resources on demand

### Example
```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [
    ConfigModule.forRoot(),
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}

// Lazy load heavy module
async function bootstrap() {
  const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule);

  const { HeavyModule } = await import('./heavy.module');
  app.use('/heavy', HeavyModule);

  await app.listen(3000);
}
```

### Object Creation
- Reuse objects when possible
- Use object pooling for frequently created objects
- Avoid creating unnecessary objects in loops

### Data Structures
- Choose appropriate data structures
- Use Sets for unique values
- Use Maps for key-value lookups
- Consider using WeakMap/WeakSet for cache

## File Operations

### File Uploads
- Stream large file uploads
- Implement chunked uploads for very large files
- Clean up temporary files

### Example
```typescript
@Post('upload')
@UseInterceptors(FileInterceptor('file'))
async uploadFile(@UploadedFile() file: Express.Multer.File) {
  // Process file
  // Clean up
  await fs.unlink(file.path);
}
```

